---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Introduction">
  <h1>primavera-ui</h1>
  <p>Primavera is a spec-first component library with plain JS web component implementations. Spec is handwritten, opinionated, and relatively informal — markdown files. Implementations are vibe-coded based on spec then tested & further refined.</p>
  <p>I am building this because I have a need for framework-free components and I believe detailed specification for human user interfaces is best human directed and LLMs can provide a good 98% translation.</p>

  <h2>Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Native web components</li>
    <li>Server Side Rendering</li>
    <li>Accessibility</li>
    <li>Optional styles</li>
    <li>No Shadow DOM</li>
    <li>Demo pages</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Getting started</h2>
  <pre><code set:html={`npm install @primavera-ui/components`} /></pre>
  <pre><code set:html={`import { register } from "@primavera-ui/components/otp";
register();`} /></pre>

  <h2>Components</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}otp`}>OTP Input</a> — One-time password input with keyboard navigation, paste support, and accessibility.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Roadmap</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Wrappers for front-end frameworks (React, SolidJS, Svelte)</li>
    <li>Drag and drop component</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  p {
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  li a {
    color: #3b82f6;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  li a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  pre {
    background: #1e1e1e;
    color: #d4d4d4;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
</style>
